OL,3,CMan sets up fundraiser for 'gentle
OL,4,Cgiant' doorman left severely disabled
OL,6,FMichael described Adrian as a "gentle
OL,7,Fgiant" who "worked city centre doors
OL,8,Ffor many years" and "worked two jobs
OL,9,Fto secure his family's living."
OL,11,FHe said: "Adrian had a stroke five or
OL,12,Fsix years ago which left him disabled,
OL,13,Fseverely in fact.
OL,15,F"His wife Tracey has cared for him
OL,16,Fever since with help from his family.
OL,18,F"It's been hard on all the family.
OL,19,FAdrian was considered the gentleman of
OL,20,Fthe doors by many and if you ever met
OL,21,Fhim you would know why.
